DateReviewed: 2026-01-02
Description: Our article today talks about a take on secrets - namely one called the Vault Secrets Operator, or VSO. The upside is that it doesn't store anything in etcd, like ordinary K8s secrets would be. We start by noting you can actually use etcd as the backend if you wish - but they recommend something more secure. They explain how you can add RBAC and access them instead through a resource, where they are more secure. They even include diagrams! They have a comparison of the pros and cons of both.
BottomLine: Good short piece on a new tech for managing Kubernetes secrets
